[3] England
Date: Thu 19 APR 2018
Source: Get Surrey [edited]
https://www.getsurrey.co.uk/news/surrey-news/measles-outbreak-redhill-reported-public-14551225


Public Health England is warning of a measles outbreak in Redhill.

There have been 34 cases -- 26 confirmed and 8 deemed to be probable cases -- since January 2018, mostly in Redhill but with some reported in other parts of Surrey and Sussex.

A further 23 people are being investigated as possible measles cases.

Public Health England South East has urged the public to ensure they are vaccinated and up-to-date with 2 doses of MMR vaccine.

[Byline: Les Steed]

