[8] Missouri (Kansas City)
Date: Thu 19 Apr 2018
Source: KCTV [edited]
http://www.kctv5.com/story/37989915/4-confirmed-measles-cases-in-kansas-city-health-department-says


A local measles outbreak is growing. The Kansas City Health Department says there have now been 4 confirmed cases in Kansas City, MO.

The department said it plans to release more information on Thu [19 Apr 2018] about the cases and where the public may have been exposed.

Meanwhile, the Liberty Public Schools District notified parents in an email Wed [18 Apr 2018] that the Clay County Health Center confirmed a case of the measles for a Kansas City resident who attends Warren Hills Elementary.

"At this time, we believe that there was no measles exposure to parents, students, staff or guests at Warren Hills Elementary during school hours," a latter from the Clay County Public Health Center said.

In addition to those 4 cases, there have been 13 cases of measles confirmed in Johnson County, KS, 2 in Linn County and one in Miami County.

[Byline: Nick Sloan]

